sentences: Rain Aladdin oglu Sultanov (born April 29, 1965) is an Azerbaijani jazz saxophonist and Honorary Artist of Azerbaijan.
Sultanov was born on April 29, 1965, in Baku.
He played at military band while being in the Soviet Army for four years.
Continuing his musical education at Asaf Zeynally Music School in Baku, Sultanov took the first place at the Republican Contest among specialized schools, in 1985.
In 1988, Sultanov worked at State Song Theatre on Rashid Behbudov’s invitation and performed compositions of Charlie Parker and Michael Brecker.
He entered Azerbaijan State Conservatoire in the same year.
In 1989, Sultanov was invited to Azerbaijani State Orchestra “Gaya”.
In 1992, Sultanov was invited to work as a soloist at Estrada-Symphonic Orchestra of Azerbaijan State Broadcasting Union under the management of Faig Sujeddinov.
In 1992-94’s, Sultanov played at different jazz clubs and concert halls of Turkey and Moscow.
In 1995, Sultanov composed his first compositions called “Jokers and dance” and “Day off”.

In 1996-97's, Sultanov became a member of jazz festivals in Germany.
He composed such compositions as “Last moment”, “Crazy world” and others while being in Germany and returning to the motherland he decided to create a group called “Syndicate”.
The first solo concerts called “Last moment” of “Syndicate” group were held from July 14 to July 15, 1997.
